Introduction

Mass incarcerations isnt a phenomenon, it has been happening throughout this countrys history. African Americans have been increasingly been sent to prison throughout our history, as well as other people of color. The mass incarceration epidemic has been effecting prisoners unjustly, as well indirectly towards their family.

Data Summary

In total their have been 23,207,908 total incarcerations in the US. With black incarcerations making up 7,891,239 incarcerations. African Americans make up 5.442801% but make up 34.00237% of incarcerations. This means that black communities are being over incarcerated.

Growth of the U.S. Prison Population

After assessing this charts it seems that incarcerations have been climbing fast since the 1970, and looks like incarcerations have about quadrupled from 1970 to 2018.

Growth of Prison Population by State

When you assess this chart you can see that California has a big jump of incarcerations between 1980-1990, you can also see that Washington has being increasing their incarcerations, But New York has steadily been decreasing since the mid 1990s.
